Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.85,0:00:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for joining us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.05,0:00:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and welcome to the program!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.26,0:00:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our privilege \Nto spend the next hour \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.79,0:00:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with you dear brothers \Nand sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.79,0:00:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please join us \Non a field trip to Ethiopia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where we will meet \NBrother Stephanos Demsas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Demsas and his wife \Nserved faithfully for many years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,while the preaching work \Nwas under ban. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.01,0:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You will enjoy their experiences.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever participated \Nin a preaching campaign? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.18,0:00:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Our team was present \Nwhen one was arranged in Armenia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A preaching campaign \Nis uplifting and encouraging \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.45,0:00:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to everyone involved \Nas this segment will show.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.86,0:00:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you react \Nif one of your loved ones decides \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.69,0:00:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave the truth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.23,0:00:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It truly is heartbreaking, \Nto say the least, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but what Bible principles \Ncan help us endure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.30,0:00:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,such a challenge? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.97,0:00:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This dramatization will help us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.91,0:00:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the November program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.04,0:01:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.83,0:01:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We have selected the theme \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.26,0:01:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be a Champion of Truth!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.20,0:01:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have heard \Nof the word “champion” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,used in the context of sports. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.27,0:01:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a champion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.27,0:01:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The word \Ncan have different meanings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.74,0:01:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The word is related \Nto the French word champ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.48,0:01:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning “field.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.48,0:01:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That word has its origin \Nin the Latin word campus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,also meaning “field” \Nor “battlefield.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible speaks of \Na champion on a battlefield \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.79,0:01:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1 Samuel 17:4: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.63,0:01:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then a champion came out \Nfrom the camps of the Philistines; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,his name was Goliath.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Goliath was a champion \Nfor a wrong cause, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.41,0:02:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, \Nto take the lead in defeating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.41,0:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the ancient Israelites in battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In our modern time, \Naccording to one definition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.35,0:02:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a champion \Nis “an ardent defender \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.42,0:02:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“or supporter of a cause \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or another person.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.69,0:02:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians today \Nare ardent defenders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.56,0:02:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and supporters of the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.03,0:02:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watchtower \Nof January 15, 2012, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.77,0:02:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,said on page 8: \N“Other champions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Bible truth rose up \Nin the centuries that followed.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Years before, \NThe Watchtower said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.61,0:02:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“This magazine \Nwill never shrink in fear \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.28,0:02:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from championing the truth!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Watchtower \Nhas been championing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.62,0:02:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘the cause of Kingdom truth.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, are you a champion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.26,0:02:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sports competition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.26,0:02:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,only one individual \Ngets to be the champion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the case \Nof true Christians, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all can be champions \Nof the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All Christians \Nare to defend the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.67,0:03:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and become conquerors\N—winners.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s necessary \Nto defend the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.28,0:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because in today’s world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.28,0:03:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is being attacked \Nand distorted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We are surrounded \Nby a sea of lies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and misrepresentations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How did such lies get started? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.62,0:03:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They started in the garden of Eden \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.63,0:03:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when Satan told Eve lies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan, \Nthrough his deceptive statements, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,became “the father of the lie.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.17,0:03:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All the problems in the world\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—all calamities \N(also your personal calamities), \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all wars, \Nall diseases, all crimes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all unhappiness, \Nsorrow, and death\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.88,0:03:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—started with the original lies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.35,0:03:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in the garden of Eden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.62,0:03:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is “the father of the lie.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But today there are \Nmany “children” of the lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of us is affected. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.23,0:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We are surrounded \Nby a sea of lies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A lie is “a false statement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.17,0:04:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“deliberately presented \Nas being true; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a falsehood.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.70,0:04:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A lie is the opposite \Nof the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lying involves \Nsaying something incorrect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to a person who is entitled to know \Nthe truth about a matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is also something \Nthat is called a half-truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible tells Christians \Nto be honest with each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now that you \Nhave put away deceit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.66,0:04:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . speak truth,” \Nwrote the apostle Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at Ephesians 4:25. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lies and half-truths \Nundermine trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.93,0:04:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A German proverb says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who lies once is not believed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.34,0:04:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,even if he says the truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to speak openly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and honestly with each other, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:04:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not withholding \Nbits of information \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.11,0:05:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that could change \Nthe perception of the listener \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.85,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or mislead him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.89,0:05:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As to lies, \Nthere are different types. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.09,0:05:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Some politicians \Nhave lied about matters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.49,0:05:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they wanted to keep secret. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies sometimes lie \Nin advertisements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.96,0:05:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding their products. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the news media? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Many try to report events truthfully. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.37,0:05:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should not be gullible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and believe \Neverything newspapers write \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or everything we hear on radio \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or see on television.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.11,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are religious lies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If Satan is called \N“the father of the lie,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then Babylon the Great, \Nthe global empire of false religion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be called \Nthe “mother” of the lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Individual false religions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,could be called \N“daughters” of the lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.76,0:05:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Some lie by saying that sinners \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,will get tormented in hell forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.17,0:05:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Others lie by saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.17,0:05:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Once saved, always saved.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.51,0:06:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, others lie \Nby saying that the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will be burned up \Non Judgment Day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.45,0:06:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and all good people \Nwill go to heaven. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.45,0:06:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Some worship idols. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.79,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote at Romans 1:25: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“They exchanged \Nthe truth of God for the lie \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.79,0:06:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“and venerated \Nand rendered sacred service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.13,0:06:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to the creation \Nrather than the Creator.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.70,0:06:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are many lies \Nof a personal nature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.17,0:06:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that people express \Nin everyday life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A businessman \Nmay get a phone call \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but tell his secretary \Nto answer the caller \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by saying he is not in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.85,0:06:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This may be considered \Na small lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.98,0:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There are small lies, \Nbig lies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and malicious lies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.22,0:06:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A child may have broken something \Nbut when asked initially, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.49,0:06:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out of fear of punishment, \Ndenies having done it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This does not make the child \Na malicious liar.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, \Nwhat if an entrepreneur \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,tells his bookkeeper \Nto falsify the entries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the books \Nin order to save on taxes? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This lying to the tax office \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.45,0:07:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is certainly a serious lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a deliberate attempt \Nto mislead somebody \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that has the right to know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It also robs the government \Nof what they have established \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as legal income. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see \Nthat not all lies are the same; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.40,0:07:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there are small lies, big lies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.00,0:07:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and malicious lies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.07,0:07:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is a malicious liar. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.67,0:07:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the champion of the lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.47,0:07:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Jehovah hates liars, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.74,0:07:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we should avoid all lies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.01,0:07:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not just big or malicious lies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.21,0:07:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But can we find the truth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say, “Truth is relative.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.95,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is like saying, \N“This is truth for you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is truth for me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This claim is not logical \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.09,0:08:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to religious truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.43,0:08:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Either God is a Trinity \Nor he’s not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Either the soul is mortal \Nor it is not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Either there is a future paradise \Non earth or there is not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Either homosexuality \Nis acceptable to God or it is not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Either participating in wars \Nis permissible or it is not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.12,0:08:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is definite, not relative, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah conveyed \Nthe truth to his servants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 43:3 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.20,0:08:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Send out your light and your truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.26,0:08:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is a Revealer of truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One of several reasons \Nwhy Jesus came into the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.11,0:08:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was to “witness to the truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 18:37b, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.85,0:08:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he said: \N“For this I have been born, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.75,0:08:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“and for this \NI have come into the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I should bear witness \Nto the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:09:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone who is on the side \Nof the truth listens to my voice.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.66,0:09:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we listen to Jesus, \Nor read in the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what he taught, \Nwe can learn the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was the personification \Nof the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.67,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “I am the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.14,0:09:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the truth and the life.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.64,0:09:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can find out what the truth is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by diligently studying the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.31,0:09:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is that which is a fact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For true Christians, \Nthe entire text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Hebrew \Nand Christian Greek Scriptures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,constitutes the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.72,0:09:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 119:160 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.69,0:09:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,says of Jehovah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The essence \Nof your word is truth.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why \Nit is good to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,daily Bible reading \Nwith meditation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.30,0:09:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and weekly family worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.64,0:09:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 24:45-47, we read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that for the time of the end, \NJesus would appoint \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a “faithful and discreet slave,” \Nor Governing Body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain the Bible\Nto His followers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and help them to grow \Nin understanding of the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas Jesus’ teachings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the written Word of God \Nare inspired, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.16,0:10:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“the faithful and discreet slave” \Nis not inspired, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.43,0:10:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,although it champions the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.24,0:10:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the faithful slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,provides spiritual food. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas in the first century \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.74,0:10:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there was supernatural knowledge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.84,0:10:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,available for apostles \Nand Bible writers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.85,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the time of the end, \NJehovah does not bestow \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this miraculous gift anymore, \Nas explained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Corinthians 13:8. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Although there is \Nno divine inspiration today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,still Jesus leads \Nhis people progressively \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.93,0:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,through the services \Nof the faithful slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus trusts \Nthat the imperfect faithful slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,will do its best \Nto convey spiritual food. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.94,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you also trust the slave?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.75,0:11:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas the truth \Nof God’s Word does not change, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,our understanding \Nof the truth does change \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because we \Nare not perfect yet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.36,0:11:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We understand more \Nabout the truth today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,than Christians \Nin the first century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we keep up with the progressive\Nunderstanding of truth?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was told: \N“Many will rove about, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.70,0:11:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the true knowledge \Nwill become abundant.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.44,0:11:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a gradual process. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We are still roving about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Millennium, \NJehovah will reveal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,additional truths to mankind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.45,0:11:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At Revelation 20:12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it mentions scrolls \Nthat will be opened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle John reports \Nthat the dead are to be “judged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.99,0:11:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“out of those things \Nwritten in the scrolls \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.73,0:11:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,according to their deeds.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:11:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, then, \Nthese scrolls will contain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.54,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,additional information for mankind \Nduring the thousand years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands to reason \Nthat after the end of the Millennium, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there will be \Nadditional truths to learn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.35,0:12:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, \Naccording to Ecclesiastes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,chapter 3, verse 11: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mankind will never find out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.99,0:12:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the work \Nthat the true God has made.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do we know \Nwe have the truth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At Pentecost 33 \Nof our Common Era, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,true Christians \Nnumbered only about 3,000. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we are millions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.70,0:12:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And on average,\Nevery weekend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.04,0:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 5,000 \Nare getting baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.64,0:12:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But this in itself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.71,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is not proof \Nthat we have the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.25,0:12:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not measured \Nin numbers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.32,0:12:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we know \Nwe have the truth?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For one, \Nbecause we remain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.06,0:12:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jesus’ teaching, \NJohn 8:31. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, \Nwe know we have the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the deep bond of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.37,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for each other, John 13:35. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, we know we have the truth \Nbecause our conduct \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,adheres \Nto the high moral standards of truth,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,John 15:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.55,0:13:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourth, \Nwe know we have the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.85,0:13:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because we remain neutral \Nin the controversies of the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus advised \Nat John 17:14. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.22,0:13:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifth, \Nwe know we have the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are \NGod’s name people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.23,0:13:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts 15:14 speaks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.63,0:13:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of “a people for his name.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.57,0:13:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: \N“The truth will set you free.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It sets us free from fears\N—like the fear of death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.31,0:13:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of the future, \Nand an exaggerated fear of man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.45,0:13:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It also sets us free \Nfrom false teachings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.65,0:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from spiritism, \Nand from astrology and magic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.59,0:14:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It frees us from immorality \Nand its consequences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There are \Nno other people on earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that are \Nas spiritually free as we are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.80,0:14:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we appreciate that freedom? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.07,0:14:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth leads to freedom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Corinthians 3:17 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.14,0:14:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Where the spirit of Jehovah is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.47,0:14:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there is freedom.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth penetrates schools. \NHow so? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.08,0:14:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of our children \Nwho preach the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.75,0:14:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to classmates and to teachers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.29,0:14:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you go to school? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.29,0:14:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you champion \Nthe truth at school? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.22,0:14:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you do this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.23,0:14:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You do this not only by preaching \Nbut also by your conduct, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by your dress and grooming, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and by taking a stand for the truth \Nwhen others want you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.97,0:14:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to participate \Nin unchristian practices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You also champion the truth \Nby remaining honest \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.98,0:14:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and not cheating \Non your exams. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.51,0:14:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah \Nwill love you for that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.91,0:15:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth \Nalso penetrates prisons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.12,0:15:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports have come in \Nfrom many countries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,telling of the good work \Nbrothers are doing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in contacting prisoners \Nin various prisons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.96,0:15:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,helping some to rehabilitate \Ntheir lives spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.73,0:15:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In a number of such institutions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.83,0:15:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,regular meetings are being held \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and several prisoners \Nhave studied to the point \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of dedication and baptism.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.71,0:15:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth penetrates \Neven walls of monasteries. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.78,0:15:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In Mexico, in 2009, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a nun was baptized who, \Nbecause of the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.18,0:15:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,had left \Nher monastery and order, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.99,0:15:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,although she was \Nthe mother superior.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.99,0:15:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The world \Nis in utter confusion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blessing\Nto know the truth! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.26,0:15:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We rejoice in it! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.26,0:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the truth on our lips. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the truth around our hips. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.24,0:15:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians chapter 6 \Nsays that “the belt of truth” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.57,0:15:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is fastened around our waists. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.14,0:16:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We are ready to teach it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk the truth, \Nand we walk in the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.48,0:16:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who continue to walk \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the truth \Nwill walk in it forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.29,0:16:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Help your students \Nto love the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.09,0:16:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and to live the truth but, \Nif necessary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.96,0:16:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be willing to die \Nfor the truth and for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is invincible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and will conquer \Nthis wicked world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In some countries, \Nwe may have many enemies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who may want to silence us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.91,0:16:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But the apostle Paul said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Corinthians 13:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.88,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For we can do nothing \Nagainst the truth.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.69,0:16:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither can our enemies \Nsuppress the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.66,0:16:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we appreciate\Nthat we have the truth\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—the only truth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this arrogant to say? \NBy no means! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.46,0:16:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a sin \Nif we would not say so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was not arrogant \Nwhen he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.47,0:17:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I am the truth.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.61,0:17:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To know the truth \Nis not enough. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.94,0:17:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to champion it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.14,0:17:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are still \Nmany lovers of truth out there; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,search for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.08,0:17:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will help you\Nin the search? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.15,0:17:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,According to John 4:23, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that Jehovah \Nis searching for ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that want to worship in truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority \Nwill not listen to the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.66,0:17:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because ‘they love the darkness \Nrather than the light.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.93,0:17:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth may expose \Ntheir sinful conduct, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.14,0:17:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and they \Nmay not have the humility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to want \Nto repent and change. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.31,0:17:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have to preach to them\N—to warn them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezekiel was told: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.05,0:17:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must warn them from me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.85,0:17:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle applies to us as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul speaks of “the sword \Nof . . . God’s word.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.79,0:17:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it well \Nto champion the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.33,0:18:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Train your students \Nto be good defenders of it as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The time will come \Nin Paradise after the final test \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when it will not be necessary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.24,0:18:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to champion, \Nor defend, the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.87,0:18:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody \Nwill attack it anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.21,0:18:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, \Nwhether we are adults, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.05,0:18:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,teenagers, or children, \Nlet us follow and imitate Jesus\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.75,0:18:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—the greatest Champion of truth! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.85,0:18:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end, \Nkeep studying the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep spreading the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.73,0:18:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep loving the truth \Nand Jehovah, the God of truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold fast to the truth \Nas to a lifeline\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—as this is what it is! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.40,0:18:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,By staying faithful, \Nwhether you survive Armageddon \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.01,0:18:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or are resurrected in Paradise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be a victorious \Nchampion of the truth!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.91,0:18:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now look at some examples \Nof how our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.35,0:18:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world \Nfaithfully champion the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.19,0:18:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.42,0:19:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lösch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.42,0:19:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When a dear friend or perhaps \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,even a family member leaves the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.23,0:19:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be a very challenging situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.23,0:19:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It can truly be a test of our faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.23,0:19:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when we see something \Nlike that take place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,While watching \Nthis dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pay attention to how the mother\Nwas able to champion the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.44,0:19:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by remaining \Nloyal to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.16,0:19:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Gabriella. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben and I have always enjoyed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.26,0:19:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,attending the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.67,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But lately, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s been difficult. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.70,0:19:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Something was missing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.54,0:19:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—our son.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like watching a movie \Nof someone else’s family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.57,0:20:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe \Nthis was happening to us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our son, Levi, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.07,0:20:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was no longer \None of Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders and friends \Nin the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were so supportive \Nand understanding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them \Nwatched Levi grow up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,give his first talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.62,0:21:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,get baptized.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so torn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.98,0:21:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was disappointed in Levi \Nfor leaving Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.05,0:21:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was \Nmore disappointed in myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.69,0:21:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like we \Nfailed him somehow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept wondering \Nhow he was doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.67,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he OK?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.81,0:22:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as hard \Nas the past few weeks had been, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.41,0:22:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it just got harder.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what the Bible said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about “quit mixing in company \Nwith anyone”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.26,0:22:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who is not living \Naccording to Christian standards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.59,0:22:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never thought that scripture \Nwould one day apply to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Later that evening, \Na brother was talking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.37,0:22:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about the example \Nof Korah’s sons.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah confirmed that He \Nwas using Moses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.55,0:22:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to lead His people, \Nnot Korah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.76,0:22:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When the people were told \Nto move away \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.86,0:22:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,from the rebels’ tents, \Nwhat would Korah’s sons do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they put loyalty to family \Nahead of loyalty to Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.04,0:23:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible tells us \Nthat his sons remained loyal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.87,0:23:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah \Nand were blessed for it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.28,0:23:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, \Nafter the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.88,0:23:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Ben about the text \NI received from Levi. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.15,0:23:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him everything\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.32,0:23:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—how I missed Levi so much, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.73,0:23:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but that I also wanted to be loyal \Nto Jehovah like Korah’s sons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.23,0:23:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben admitted that he too \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.73,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,had been struggling \Nwith feelings like mine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.24,0:23:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he said something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.64,0:23:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that I hadn’t thought of. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.81,0:23:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were to stand between Levi \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.94,0:23:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the discipline he needs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.01,0:23:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we would, in effect, \Nbe blocking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.35,0:23:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,an expression of Jehovah’s love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.18,0:23:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from reaching him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.25,0:24:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \Nit’s our very loyalty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.36,0:24:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah \Nthat could save his life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.66,0:24:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We agreed to continue \Nto put our trust \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.66,0:24:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah \Nand stay loyal to him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been five years now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.72,0:24:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and while Levi \Nstill hasn’t returned to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.86,0:24:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t given up hope on him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.56,0:24:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Until that day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.00,0:24:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m staying busy as a regular pioneer \Nand focusing my energies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.40,0:24:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on helping others \Nlearn about Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.57,0:24:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve come to experience firsthand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.24,0:24:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of Psalm 97:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.98,0:25:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah really does guard \Nhis loyal ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.43,0:25:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped Gabriella overcome \Nthis difficult challenge? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.10,0:25:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when she received\Na text message from her son, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.50,0:25:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,she applied Scriptural counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.50,0:25:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to her personal circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.74,0:25:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The good example of Korah’s sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,gave her added motivation \Nso as not to allow \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.14,0:25:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,her feelings for her son \Nto dictate her actions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.85,0:25:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, she was firm \Nin her loyalty to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.99,0:25:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, her husband, Ben, \Nhad found an article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.66,0:25:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that helped \Nthe two of them appreciate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that they should make sure \Nnot to stand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.06,0:25:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,between Jehovah \Nand their son, Levi. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.13,0:25:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they wanted \NJehovah’s expression of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.80,0:25:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach Levi.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.87,0:25:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever we \Nare faced with a trial, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.64,0:25:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to remember \Nto pray constantly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.34,0:26:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah for guidance \Nand to look for Jehovah’s counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.98,0:26:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in our literature \Nand during our meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.62,0:26:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul faced \Nmany challenges in his ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.35,0:26:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2 Corinthians chapter 11, \Nstarting in verse 23, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.56,0:26:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he enumerates \Nover 20 hardships \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.96,0:26:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that he experienced \Nin his ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.83,0:26:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped Paul \Nto keep his motivation strong \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.37,0:26:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,despite everything he faced? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.77,0:26:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In this morning worship \Nfrom Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.17,0:26:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother John Ekrann highlights \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.17,0:26:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what Paul himself said \Nkept him going.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.58,0:26:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look \Nat the words in the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.78,0:26:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that the apostle Paul worded things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.85,0:26:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he said: “I live by faith \Nin the Son of God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.25,0:26:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who loved me \Nand handed himself over for me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.95,0:26:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can really see \Nthe very personal nature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.62,0:26:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ransom to the apostle Paul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.96,0:26:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s important for us to do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.96,0:26:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—as our commenters \Npointed out nicely—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.56,0:26:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it is important for us \Nto personalize the ransom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.97,0:27:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul, in Hebrews 6:5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.70,0:27:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,showed the very personal nature; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.04,0:27:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he understood the personal nature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.04,0:27:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Bible and the ransom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.11,0:27:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In Hebrews 6:5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.81,0:27:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he uses this expression: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.95,0:27:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“And who have tasted \Nthe fine word of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.52,0:27:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and powers \Nof the coming system of things.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.22,0:27:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s interesting \Nhe used the word “taste.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.36,0:27:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Taste is something very personal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.09,0:27:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody can’t taste \Nsomething for you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to put it \Nin your mouth in order \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.56,0:27:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to really know \Nwhat it’s going to taste like.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.67,0:27:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, too, with the ransom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.67,0:27:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And what practical ways \Ncan we “taste,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.71,0:27:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or personalize, \Nthe ransom for us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.91,0:27:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just consider \Na couple this morning.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.31,0:27:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One is personal fears. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.91,0:27:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Does God really love me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.98,0:27:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I worthy of love?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.05,0:27:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the “what-ifs” \Nand their cousins, the “could-bes,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.52,0:27:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they come to live and never leave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.92,0:27:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if bad things \Nor trials or difficulties happen to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.46,0:28:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to reason, \N‘Well, Jehovah God maybe doesn’t love me.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.26,0:28:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s really strong reason for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.27,0:28:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to somehow believe \Nin cause and effect. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.40,0:28:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the cause of things and effect,\Nand so after a while, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.44,0:28:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that happens to us, \Nwe begin to look at some cause \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.57,0:28:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and even begin to think \Nthat maybe Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.24,0:28:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t love us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.65,0:28:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we’re a good person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and bad things happen to us, \Nwe begin to wonder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.39,0:28:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Others my age are healthy.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.82,0:28:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Some leaving \Nor changing assignments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.89,0:28:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear everything \Nfalls into place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for them within a few weeks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.03,0:28:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m still looking for a job. \NI’m still looking for work.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.63,0:28:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, \Ndo not try to reason \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.37,0:28:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that just because things \Ndon’t work out perfectly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.77,0:28:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah doesn’t love us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.84,0:28:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.04,0:28:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We can still be doing very, \Nvery good things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.71,0:28:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet some difficulties \Ncan face us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.71,0:28:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nyou’re driving down the road, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.71,0:28:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,obeying all the traffic laws. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull up to a red light, \Nyou stop, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.99,0:29:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it turns green, you go through it, \Nand you get broadsided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.59,0:29:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by some knucklehead who went \Nthrough the red light on the other side.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.76,0:29:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s not your fault. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.23,0:29:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to say: \N“Well, you know what? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.26,0:29:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not going to obey traffic laws anymore.\NSee, it doesn’t pay!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.27,0:29:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.54,0:29:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his fault for running \Nthrough the traffic light. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.07,0:29:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes bad, or difficult, \Nthings can happen to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.78,0:29:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not our fault \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.78,0:29:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or it’s not any sign \Nthat Jehovah doesn’t love us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.25,0:29:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can reflecting \Non the ransom help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.85,0:29:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when we have these kinds \Nof personal fears?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.72,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we could start with, \NWhy do we have the ransom? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because some very bad things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.09,0:29:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,were happening \Nto some good people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.09,0:29:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—us—\NAdam and Eve’s descendants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.10,0:29:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, \NAdam sinned and Eve sinned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.00,0:29:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yet we suffer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.00,0:29:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The ransom is Jehovah’s solution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.67,0:29:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who appreciate it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.71,0:29:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s his way of telling us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.71,0:29:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know bad things are happening, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.71,0:29:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m working to fix it.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.98,0:30:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, when we reflect \Non the reason \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.48,0:30:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,why Jehovah God \Ngave us the ransom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.12,0:30:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it helps us to know \Nthat Jehovah knows we suffer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.59,0:30:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from cancer and old age \Nand the sins and mistakes of others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.99,0:30:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and even our own imperfections. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.69,0:30:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See, tasting of the ransom in this way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,means we’ll not get the feeling \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.23,0:30:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah doesn’t love us \Nwhen trials befall us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.24,0:30:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To the contrary, the ransom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.67,0:30:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is the greatest expression \Nof Jehovah’s and Jesus’ love for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.67,0:30:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and their desire to fix \Nthe current mess we live in now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.68,0:30:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How about, \Nlet’s consider a second way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could reflect \Non the ransom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.02,0:30:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the death \Nof someone close to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.55,0:30:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who’s had someone \Nvery close to them die \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.69,0:30:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,knows the very helpless feeling \Nthat you have, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.76,0:30:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that there’s \Nreally nothing you can do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.50,0:30:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant when they die, \Nyour hope\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.73,0:30:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—your faith in the resurrection \Nbased on the ransom—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.74,0:30:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more real to you \Nthan any time in your entire life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.48,0:31:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In Acts 17:31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.51,0:31:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in a beautiful speech \Nthat the apostle Paul gave, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.92,0:31:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he highlights \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.92,0:31:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus’ death \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.65,0:31:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and resurrection and the ransom \Nwas really a guarantee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.72,0:31:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.76,0:31:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in Acts 17:31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.43,0:31:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he says: “Because he has set a day \Non which he purposes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.60,0:31:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“to judge the inhabited earth \Nin righteousness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.30,0:31:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“by a man \Nwhom he has appointed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.97,0:31:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he has provided \Na guarantee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.64,0:31:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“to all men \Nby resurrecting him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.18,0:31:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the dead.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.21,0:31:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So personalizing the ransom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.41,0:31:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that it makes possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.52,0:31:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to know that the resurrection is, \Nnot just possible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.12,0:31:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but that Jehovah \Nand Jesus want to resurrect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.12,0:31:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,our mother, our father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.19,0:31:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,our beloved husband or a wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.73,0:31:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They care about each person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.50,0:31:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that has ever lived or died \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.43,0:32:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and know them \Nso intimately and so completely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.10,0:32:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can resurrect them completely \Nwith all their memories \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.17,0:32:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and personality completely \Nas we knew them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.51,0:32:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how much more personal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.98,0:32:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,could God’s love for us \Nbecome than that?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.32,0:32:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, to bring our loved ones \Nback from the dead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.95,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate statement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.42,0:32:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s personal interest \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.22,0:32:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in each and every human being. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.93,0:32:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not just collateral damage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.60,0:32:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in Satan’s war on Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.27,0:32:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The ransom is the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.64,0:32:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah plans \Nto undo all the harm \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.11,0:32:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that Satan has caused \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.11,0:32:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,since the death of Adam and Eve. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.18,0:32:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the resurrection \Nis really Jehovah’s way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.68,0:32:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of proving all of Satan’s lies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.25,0:32:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,completely false. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.39,0:32:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think about it today, \NSatan can perpetrate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.06,0:32:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of lies about what happens \Nto people after they die. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.86,0:32:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘They’re going to go here, \Nthey’re going to go there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.33,0:33:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,‘they’re going to go to some afterlife, \Nthey’re going to go to some paradise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.93,0:33:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re going to come back \Nas some animal.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.73,0:33:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the new world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.77,0:33:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when the vast majority of people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.97,0:33:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,have been resurrected, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.17,0:33:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that lie isn’t going \Nto be sold anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.38,0:33:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one can tell everyone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to them \Nwhen they died\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.78,0:33:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—nothing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.05,0:33:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,no afterlife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.38,0:33:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone will know \Nthat it’s nonexistence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.29,0:33:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That lie won’t work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.49,0:33:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jehovah knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.76,0:33:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would hurt terribly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.63,0:33:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,at the death of loved ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.70,0:33:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so he gave us the ransom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.47,0:33:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as his way of telling us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.67,0:33:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know it hurts, \Nbut please know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.34,0:33:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have \Nthe perfect solution in mind.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.11,0:33:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’ve just considered two ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.91,0:33:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to reflect and meditate on the ransom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.98,0:33:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,like the apostle Paul did, \Nto really personalize it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.98,0:33:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We just talked about personal fears \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.25,0:34:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the resurrection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.46,0:34:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the death of someone close to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.76,0:34:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how many more ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.16,0:34:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we can benefit today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.60,0:34:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from meditating on the ransom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.60,0:34:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it affects us personally.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.04,0:34:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As ministers of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.04,0:34:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we take part in preaching \Nthe good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.91,0:34:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That good news includes \Nthe wonderful provision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.75,0:34:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ransom \NBrother Ekrann highlighted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.58,0:34:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever participated \Nin a preaching campaign? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.32,0:34:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you \Nhave enjoyed campaigns \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.85,0:34:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,such as inviting \Nour neighbors to the Memorial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.49,0:34:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or the regional convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.49,0:34:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,On occasion, \Nother campaigns are approved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.50,0:34:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Service Committee \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.86,0:34:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when there is a specific need \Nin an area or language group. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.97,0:34:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We bring you a report \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.20,0:34:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on a special campaign \Nin Armenia.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.78,0:34:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Armenia is an ancient country \Nwith rich history, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.18,0:35:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,situated in the lands \Nof Mount Ararat.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.49,0:35:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Caucasus region, \NLake Sevan \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.89,0:35:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered to be \Na prized jewel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.63,0:35:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Diversity of its flora and fauna \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.96,0:35:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,contribute to the unique \Nand beautiful countryside.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.40,0:35:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yerevan, the capital, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.84,0:35:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is a modern metropolis \Nwith picturesque views \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that remind many of Paris \Nwith its trees, cafés, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.91,0:35:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and beautiful water fountains.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.25,0:35:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, a special three-week \Npreaching campaign took place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.43,0:35:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Groups of Armenian-speaking \NJehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.20,0:35:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from six different countries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.76,0:35:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,wholeheartedly responded \Nto the invitation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.01,0:36:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The main purpose of the campaign \Nwas to cover as many\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.51,0:36:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 512 unassigned territories\Nas possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.68,0:36:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Kingdom good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.85,0:36:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, an opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.85,0:36:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for an interchange \Nof encouragement was created \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.22,0:36:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for both the local friends \Nand the campaign participants.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.86,0:36:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They were warmly greeted \Nat the airport \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.36,0:36:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by local brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.60,0:36:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Witnesses made good use \Nof their tablets and smartphones to show\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.41,0:36:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,videos from the jw.org website.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.24,0:36:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Armenia is also currently home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.08,0:36:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to over 11,000 Western-Armenian refugees.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A special effort was made \Nto share with these individuals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.32,0:36:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the positive message of hope\Nand peace from the Bible\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.46,0:36:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in their native tongue, \NWest Armenian.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.79,0:36:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Metropolitan witnessing \Nserved as an effective way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.16,0:36:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach these ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.57,0:37:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first time in my life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.80,0:37:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that I participated in public witnessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.17,0:37:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was very encouraging. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.17,0:37:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When individuals would approach us \Nand show interest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.94,0:37:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I could explain to them \Nthe truth in their own language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.65,0:37:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.65,0:37:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been very heartwarming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.82,0:37:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,People have really responded well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.49,0:37:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They were in need of comfort\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.12,0:37:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the good news, especially those that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.69,0:37:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we came for,\Nthe Western Armenians. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.99,0:37:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much every door invited us in, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.66,0:37:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were very hospitable \Nand receptive.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.93,0:37:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,After we heard the announcement \Nabout the special campaign \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.83,0:37:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western language \Nthat’s going to take place in Armenia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.17,0:37:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we said: “We cannot miss this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.17,0:37:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have to be there \Nand bring our share \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.17,0:37:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in this very joyful\Npreaching campaign.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.51,0:37:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,During the three-week campaign, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.81,0:37:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,over 15,000 pieces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.88,0:37:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of Bible-based literature \Nwere left with interested ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.18,0:37:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and over 200 Bible studies \Nwere started.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.52,0:37:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very happy to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.96,0:37:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,how many brothers and sisters \Nwere ready to come \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.86,0:38:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for the campaign in Armenia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.86,0:38:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from different countries \Naround the world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.50,0:38:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That response showed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.50,0:38:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah has blessed our efforts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.87,0:38:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who came from far and wide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.04,0:38:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,greatly appreciated the share \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.14,0:38:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they had in this special event.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.38,0:38:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was so happy to see us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.98,0:38:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we were giving them a Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.05,0:38:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,they were so excited to find answers\Nfrom their own Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.99,0:38:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so blessed to be here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.22,0:38:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been the best vacation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.22,0:38:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have had as a family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.83,0:38:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I came to Armenia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.50,0:38:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it was in 1982. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.66,0:38:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked for the Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.83,0:38:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I hardly found just a few. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.00,0:38:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that I came \Nfor this campaign, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.34,0:38:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we have 11,000 Witnesses! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.41,0:38:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really so happy! \NI really want to come back!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.55,0:38:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is our hope that Jehovah God \Ncontinues to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.22,0:38:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all sorts of people to be saved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.72,0:39:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and come \Nto an accurate knowledge of truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.40,0:39:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,While we \Nenjoy relative freedom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.40,0:39:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in many countries \Naround the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.67,0:39:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at times governments \Nimpose bans \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.20,0:39:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or restrictions \Non the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.74,0:39:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Stephanos Demsas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.74,0:39:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,serves as a special pioneer \Nin Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.54,0:39:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,along with his wife, Leteberhan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.41,0:39:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Their faith was tested \Nduring many years of adversity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.35,0:39:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped them \Nchampion the truth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.82,0:39:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Their story began \Nin what is today Eritrea.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.03,0:39:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I come from a family \Nof nine children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.30,0:39:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I joined the navy in 1956. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.24,0:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was during the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.50,0:39:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when Eritrea was part of Ethiopia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.17,0:39:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother Gebrehiwot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.24,0:39:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,asked me to come to Asmara. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.81,0:39:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was studying the Bible \Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.08,0:40:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so impressed \Nwith what he shared with me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.22,0:40:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that for the rest of my vacation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.49,0:40:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible study became my priority. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.32,0:40:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, \NI was discharged from the navy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.59,0:40:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and started working \Nin Addis Ababa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.93,0:40:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was able to continue studying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.99,0:40:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible and get baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.43,0:40:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Leti was also doing the same.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.44,0:40:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1960, \NI was attending a nursing college. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.51,0:40:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There, a nurse shared \Nsome interesting thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.71,0:40:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with me from the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.88,0:40:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten other student nurses \Nalso showed interest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.55,0:40:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But the college \Nthreatened us with dismissal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.62,0:40:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because there was a ban \Non Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.63,0:40:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were shown from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.89,0:40:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,why true Christians are persecuted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.96,0:40:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we renewed our determination. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.57,0:40:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, \Nfive of us were baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.20,0:40:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, I met Stephanos, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.34,0:41:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were married in 1964.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.44,0:41:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the ban, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.45,0:41:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers were meeting \Nin small groups. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.05,0:41:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trust was in Jehovah, \Nand we made the preaching work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.45,0:41:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a matter of prayer, \Nconfident that he would help us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.42,0:41:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw evidence of this \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.62,0:41:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with the underground production \Nof The Watchtower.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.73,0:41:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers were of modest means, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.20,0:41:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but they used what they had to buy \Na hand-operated duplicating machine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.87,0:41:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which was used in our home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.80,0:41:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After returning\Nfrom our secular work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Leti and I would get busy \Nmaking copies of The Watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.77,0:41:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We would play music\Nso our neighbors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.91,0:41:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn’t hear the sound\Nof the duplicator.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.88,0:41:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1974, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.88,0:41:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Haile Selassie was deposed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.09,0:41:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This Communist government quickly began \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.42,0:41:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a campaign called “Red Terror” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.09,0:41:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,against any supposed political opposer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.69,0:41:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just having a typewriter \Nor a duplicating machine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.60,0:42:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,could put you in prison \Nor even have you killed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.47,0:42:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Picking up a paper\Nfrom the street \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.47,0:42:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with something printed on it \Nagainst the government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.74,0:42:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,could put one’s life in danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.08,0:42:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was common \Nfor people to disappear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.61,0:42:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, my youngest brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.35,0:42:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eyob, was a victim. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.55,0:42:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He disappeared on his way home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.12,0:42:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and was never seen again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.06,0:42:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,With the situation\Nbeing very dangerous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.70,0:42:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we were quite concerned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.70,0:42:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,raising our daughter, Janet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we fully trusted in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.64,0:42:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we felt his loving protection.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.41,0:42:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,From time to time,\Nsections of the city \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.74,0:42:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,were suddenly blockaded.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.95,0:42:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened one morning \Nas a translator \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.98,0:42:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was heading to our home \Nto deliver stencils for printing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.92,0:42:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Urgently, he telephoned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.32,0:42:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,informing us \Nthat a house-to-house search\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.69,0:42:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was under way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.26,0:43:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our house was full of publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.23,0:43:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,along with a duplicator\Nand typewriters!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.20,0:43:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just after the phone call, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.70,0:43:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,three soldiers \Nentered our compound to search.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.51,0:43:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.51,0:43:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed silently \Nthat Jehovah would blind them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.51,0:43:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Entering the room \Nwhere the duplicator \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.05,0:43:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and stacks \Nof freshly printed literature were, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.68,0:43:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,one soldier asked, \N“What is all this?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.62,0:43:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh, this is a duplicator that we use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.39,0:43:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to print these Bible materials.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.39,0:43:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Completing his search, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.39,0:43:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he went outside\Nto the commander, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.50,0:43:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who asked him,\N“What did you find?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.30,0:43:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To our utter amazement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.30,0:43:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,after seeing everything, \Nhe answered: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.04,0:43:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nothing! \NWe won’t find anything here.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.97,0:43:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 1970’s \Nand into the early 80’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.11,0:43:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,another wave \Nof vicious persecution occurred. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.38,0:43:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A number of faithful brothers \Nwere imprisoned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.25,0:43:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,tortured, and murdered. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.62,0:44:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taken from my work place \Nbecause of my neutral stand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.92,0:44:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and put in prison.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.59,0:44:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think about living through \Nthose difficult times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.33,0:44:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I am reminded of Isaiah 54:17 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.87,0:44:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jehovah promised us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.94,0:44:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“No weapon formed against you\N will have any success.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.87,0:44:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, in 1991, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.91,0:44:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a liberal government came to power. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.01,0:44:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave us legal recognition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.55,0:44:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and freedom of worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.09,0:44:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With these difficult, \Ndangerous years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.82,0:44:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now behind us, \Nwe were assigned to the circuit work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.22,0:44:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Eritrea and Ethiopia.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.83,0:44:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,By now, Eritrea was becoming \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.83,0:44:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,an independent country, \Nand this brought about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.47,0:44:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,new challenges for the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.47,0:44:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Some young brothers \Nwere arrested and imprisoned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.50,0:44:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their Christian stand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.77,0:44:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote at Hebrews 13:3: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.04,0:44:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep in mind those in prison, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.18,0:45:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as though you were imprisoned with them.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.35,0:45:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After enjoying the circuit work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.35,0:45:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for 15 years, \Nwe faced another change. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.15,0:45:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We were invited to serve at Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.79,0:45:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as full-time commuters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.99,0:45:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What has helped us to endure \Nthrough the ban years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.80,0:45:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to adjust to the many changes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.73,0:45:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is our spiritual study program.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.74,0:45:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re in full agreement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.74,0:45:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jeremiah 17:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.34,0:45:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Blessed is the man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.34,0:45:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who puts his trust in Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.48,0:45:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It also brings us much happiness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.11,0:45:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to know that our daughter, Janet, \Nhas been serving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.32,0:45:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as a regular pioneer \Nfor 20 years now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.46,0:45:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Each assignment\Nhas had its challenges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.99,0:45:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but many rewards and blessings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.26,0:45:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not young anymore; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.26,0:45:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m 77 years old.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.36,0:45:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m 74 years old.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.37,0:45:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We are now serving\Nas special pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.04,0:45:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think about all the changes \Nthat we’ve been through, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we realize \Nthat the words at Isaiah 6:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.54,0:46:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! Send me!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.55,0:46:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are, not just for young people, \Nbut for all of us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.78,0:46:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It is very encouraging to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.89,0:46:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephanos \Nand Leteberhan’s determination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.56,0:46:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay faithful to Jehovah, \Ncome what may. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.63,0:46:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that Jehovah \Nlooks with delight \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.96,0:46:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on their many years of service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.56,0:46:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our brothers in Canada \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.77,0:46:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,underwent similar persecution. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.17,0:46:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah help them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.37,0:46:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay special attention \Nto the numerous acts of courage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.91,0:46:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed by these \Nchampions of truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.58,0:46:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Preaching in the province of Quebec \Nwas a real challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.38,0:46:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Catholic Church \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.92,0:46:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was present \Nin every sphere of public life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.99,0:46:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the early ’40s,\Nthe persecution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.09,0:46:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,took on quite a bit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.36,0:46:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of emphasis. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.16,0:46:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Many Witnesses were being arrested. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.43,0:47:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Any excuse was used. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.93,0:47:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Peddling without a license\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.34,0:47:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—this was a favorite excuse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.34,0:47:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses were put in prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.88,0:47:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever they were seen \Nwith religious literature.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.11,0:47:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It had got so bad in Quebec \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.25,0:47:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was decided to circulate a petition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.15,0:47:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and this petition was circulated \Nthroughout Canada. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.66,0:47:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And it called \Non the government of Quebec \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.53,0:47:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to put an end \Nto this persecution. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.33,0:47:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.33,0:47:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,some 600,000 people \Nsigned the petition.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.67,0:47:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Witnesses distributed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.27,0:47:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a very fiery tract \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.27,0:47:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,called the Burning Hate of Quebec. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.28,0:47:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this tract, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.84,0:47:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they showed \Nwhat was really happening\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.55,0:47:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—the actions of the policemen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.08,0:47:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the illegal arrests, \Nthe mob action. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.82,0:47:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Within four months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.82,0:47:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there were 800 new court cases. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.99,0:48:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So here, \Nfor 400 Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.13,0:48:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you had 1,600 court cases.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.53,0:48:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The seriousness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.53,0:48:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the court cases increased, \Nin that now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.00,0:48:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they were accusing \Nthe brothers of sedition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.07,0:48:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If convicted, \Nit was more than 10\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.08,0:48:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—maybe 12 or 15—\Nyears in prison.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.68,0:48:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We had one brother,\NAimé Boucher, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.01,0:48:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who was arrested \Nand charged with sedition.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.95,0:48:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Aimé Boucher \Nwas a very poor brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.62,0:48:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who lived \Nin a rural part of Quebec. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.89,0:48:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And he actually \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.56,0:48:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,went to court \Nwith his ox and buggy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.93,0:48:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the way to court, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.93,0:48:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,he was preaching, \Nso he was arrested again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.93,0:48:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They had the court hearing, \Nand he was condemned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.14,0:48:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was found guilty of sedition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.04,0:48:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And his case went up \Nto the Court of Appeal\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.91,0:48:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—and at that time, the Court of Appeal \Nof Quebec was very hostile—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.78,0:48:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and he lost on appeal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.18,0:48:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so it went up \Nto the Supreme Court of Canada. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.89,0:49:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And by this time,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.42,0:49:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there were several \Nother brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.29,0:49:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,also charged on sedition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.76,0:49:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which meant that if he lost his case, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.30,0:49:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we had several going to prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.30,0:49:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for very lengthy prison terms.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.57,0:49:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When Brother Boucher’s case \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.90,0:49:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,came before the Supreme Court, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.44,0:49:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he lost by a majority of one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.78,0:49:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Catholic judges \Nall ruled against him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.45,0:49:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they found that the tract \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.78,0:49:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the Burning Hate of Quebec \Nwas seditious.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.85,0:49:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lawyers looked at the situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.72,0:49:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,prayed about it, and thought: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.19,0:49:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What can we do? \NWe can’t lose this battle.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they realized that in Canada \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.96,0:49:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a very rarely used provision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.63,0:49:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of asking the Supreme Court \Nfor a rehearing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.57,0:49:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At the rehearing, \None of the Catholic judges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.57,0:49:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was willing to discuss further \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.57,0:49:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the issue of sedition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.61,0:49:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And to be guilty of sedition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.21,0:50:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to incite to violence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.62,0:50:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So our attorney asked them: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.69,0:50:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please, look at the record. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.75,0:50:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Show the court \Nwhere Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.92,0:50:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,incited to violence.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.93,0:50:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, they were able \Nto convince a court they were wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.36,0:50:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they overturned \Ntheir initial decision, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.96,0:50:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother Boucher’s case \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.30,0:50:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was victorious.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.30,0:50:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This dealt with all \Nthe accusations of sedition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.51,0:50:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and really brought to an end \Nthe vicious opposition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.98,0:50:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because that case \Nwas the one the government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.58,0:50:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was hoping would work out for them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.05,0:50:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one case \Nthat’s quite noteworthy in Quebec. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.72,0:50:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s a case of the priest \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.62,0:50:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,calling up the federal police \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.56,0:50:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to come and interrupt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.60,0:50:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a meeting of Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.17,0:50:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and expel the speaker \Nfrom the province of Quebec. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.27,0:51:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The police obeyed the priest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.61,0:51:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They went to the meeting, \Nthey took the brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.41,0:51:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and they escorted him \Nout of the province into Ontario.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.61,0:51:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And to disrupt a religious meeting \Nwas a criminal act. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.49,0:51:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time\N—and it’s at the level of the Supreme Court—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.32,0:51:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they found that the three policemen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.66,0:51:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,had to pay moral damages \Nto the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.16,0:51:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for intercepting, \Nor interrupting, the meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.30,0:51:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This has never happened before.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.23,0:51:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it came up \Nto the Supreme Court, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.50,0:51:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they unanimously ruled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.04,0:51:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,against the province of Quebec. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.17,0:51:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The section on religious freedom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.98,0:51:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is the result of these court cases. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.45,0:51:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Every lawyer in Canada \N(whether in Quebec or in English Canada), \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.05,0:51:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when he studies law, \Nmust review these cases. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.92,0:51:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the fundamentals \Nof religious freedom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.32,0:51:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And they represent \Nthe different areas\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.73,0:51:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—police action, government action, \Ncriminal action—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.73,0:52:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and they lay a very nice basis \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.47,0:52:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for our freedoms today.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.94,0:52:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Our purpose is to be able \Nto preach the good news \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.21,0:52:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and to direct people’s attention \Ntoward the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.95,0:52:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But our court cases \Nhave helped governments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.48,0:52:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,courts, judges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.49,0:52:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and officials \Nto have the right point of view \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.42,0:52:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on the issue of religious freedom.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.40,0:52:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The endurance and hard work \Nof our brothers in Quebec \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.46,0:52:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,truly resulted in a witness \Nto the nations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.40,0:52:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,While the hope \Nfor a positive outcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.14,0:52:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,can at times provide us \Nwith needed motivation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.14,0:52:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we can’t always expect support \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.21,0:52:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from the authorities \Nin this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.05,0:52:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The same applies \Nin many areas of life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.78,0:52:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever trials we may face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.12,0:52:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you have lost \Na loved one in death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.65,0:52:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking forward to a time \Njust around the corner \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.66,0:52:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us endure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.66,0:53:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s also the title \Nof this month’s music video, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.73,0:53:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just Around the Corner.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.14,0:53:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear the songbirds singing,\NAnd you watch the clouds roll by.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.22,0:53:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you’re walking in the valley\NAs the sun shines in a clear blue sky.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.32,0:53:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re welcoming your loved ones,\NAnd you can’t believe your eyes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.90,0:53:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this earthly Paradise\NWas just around the corner.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.38,0:53:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a house down in the valley\NAnd a house high on the hill.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.72,0:54:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is singing by the river\NAs the water flows and turns the mill.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.56,0:54:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The golden fields are waiting.\NLet the harvesting begin.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.47,0:54:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the world we’re living in\NWas just around the corner.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.14,0:54:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s great to share with friends who care\NThe things that we looked forward to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.32,0:54:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now every tear has disappeared.\NThe world is young, and life is new.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.33,0:54:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s the sound of happy voices\NAnd the scent of new mown hay.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.93,0:54:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you’re calling to your loved ones\NAs you start another perfect day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.34,0:55:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we thank our God, Jehovah,\NFor his tender loving care.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.68,0:55:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the blessings we all share\NWere just around the corner.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.29,0:55:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And evʹry day I smile and say,\N“How good to see your happy face!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.37,0:55:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,ʹCause once, it seemed, I only dreamed\NThat you’d be in my warm embrace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.54,0:55:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting ʹround the corner\NIs a world I long to see.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.11,0:55:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a promise from Jehovah.\NIt’s a guaranteed reality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.29,0:55:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s hard to get downhearted\NWhen I think of what’s in store.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.30,0:55:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the day I’m waiting for,\NAnd it’s just around the corner.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.98,0:56:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful song! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.39,0:56:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I lost my father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.99,0:56:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was two years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.99,0:56:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a soldier in World War II \Nand was killed in battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.66,0:56:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had an opportunity \Nto get to know him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.06,0:56:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up, \NI missed having a father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.00,0:56:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because I saw \Neveryone else had one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.60,0:56:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I look forward to observing \Nthe earthly resurrection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.61,0:56:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing my physical father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.84,0:56:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I hope that both he \Nand my mother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.51,0:56:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,will want to worship \NJehovah in Paradise.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.92,0:56:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing that, \NBrother Lösch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.52,0:56:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When my father comes back \Nin the resurrection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.45,0:56:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to welcoming him \Nwith open arms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.06,0:56:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a keen student \Nof history and the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.39,0:56:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and so he will want to know \Nall about what took place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.10,0:56:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,during this time of the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.10,0:57:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So my family and I \Nwill have a good time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.50,0:57:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,filling him in on what took place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.70,0:57:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This music video \Nand some of the videos we’ve seen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.77,0:57:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the past few years \Nat regional conventions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.48,0:57:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have painted such a clear picture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.48,0:57:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the hope we have for the future. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.68,0:57:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we work hard \Nas champions of the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.55,0:57:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that hope will become \Na reality very soon.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.35,0:57:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well said. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.36,0:57:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of champions \Nof the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.69,0:57:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we would like \Nto conclude this program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.69,0:57:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with greetings from our brothers \Nand sisters in Romania, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.13,0:57:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a country situated \Nin the southeast of Europe.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.77,0:57:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you may know Romania \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.27,0:57:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for its traditional instrument \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.04,0:57:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,called the nai, or pan flute. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.54,0:57:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s made of wood \Nand has around 20 pipes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.81,0:57:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,arranged in a curved array. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.21,0:57:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The pitch is adjusted \Nwith beeswax, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.02,0:57:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is introduced \Nin the pipes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.42,0:57:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.45,0:57:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Certeze North Congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.46,0:57:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the north of Romania, \Nsend us their love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.83,0:58:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The congregation is located \Nnear the Ukrainian border, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.53,0:58:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an area known \Nfor its brightly colored folk costumes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.30,0:58:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The congregation \Nis made up of families \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.57,0:58:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with many generations \Nof Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.31,0:58:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so they have been \Nchampions of truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.41,0:58:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.41,0:58:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth reached this area \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.41,0:58:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about 80 years ago, \Nand now the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.88,0:58:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is made up of 126 publishers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.52,0:58:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They conduct \Nabout 90 Bible studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.25,0:58:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of which many \Nattend the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.92,0:58:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is \Na large concentration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.46,0:58:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of Witnesses in the area, \Nthe congregation territory \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.66,0:58:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is only five kilometers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.73,0:58:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or a little over three miles, \Nfrom the one end to the other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.10,0:58:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Each territory card \Nhas only about five houses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.24,0:58:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, \Nthe congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.54,0:58:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,regularly assists \Nwith working territory \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.88,0:58:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 200 kilometers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.58,0:58:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or about 124 miles away.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.71,0:58:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.72,0:58:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Certeze North Congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.25,0:59:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,send all of you \Nchampions of the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.06,0:59:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,their love and greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.66,0:59:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and so do all of us \Nat world headquarters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.19,0:59:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \Nin Brooklyn, New York.\N
